The President may appoint, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, an Associate Attorney General.
(Added Pub. L. 95–139, § 1(a), Oct. 19, 1977, 91 Stat. 1171.)</akn:p></akn:content></akn:section></akn:body></akn:act></akn:akomaNtoso>